# Project Overview

This is a chat DApp (Decentralized Application) built with:
- [Tauri](mdc:https:/tauri.app) - Rust-based framework for building desktop applications
- [SvelteKit](mdc:https:/kit.svelte.dev) - Web framework for building Svelte applications
- [TypeScript](mdc:https:/www.typescriptlang.org) - Typed JavaScript

## Key Files and Directories

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project configuration and dependencies
- [src/](mdc:src) - Frontend code (SvelteKit)
  - [src/routes/+page.svelte](mdc:src/routes/+page.svelte) - Main application page
- [src-tauri/](mdc:src-tauri) - Backend code (Rust/Tauri)
  - [src-tauri/src/lib.rs](mdc:src-tauri/src/lib.rs) - Main Rust backend logic
  - [src-tauri/src/main.rs](mdc:src-tauri/src/main.rs) - Rust entry point

## Development Workflow

1. Run `yarn dev` to start the development server for the frontend
2. Run `yarn tauri dev` to start the full application with Tauri backend
